	<h1>Black Lives Matter Protests</h1>

	<p> The United States has a long history of social and political movements that have led to major protests throughout the country including the Black Lives Matter Protests, which began on Wednesday, July 5, 1905. It occurred in various cities and was sparked by: Police brutality and systemic racism. The protest led to increased public awareness and activism against racism.</p>

